conversationStarters.title: Exploring Together: Chrome Browser
conversationStarters.message: Chrome Browser has captured their attention (2 times). Let's explore why!
conversationStarters.actionSuggestion: Say: 'I'd love to understand Chrome Browser better. Could you give me a quick tour of what you do there?'
deeperQuestions: What's your favorite feature and why?
If you could change one thing about it, what would it be?
Are there other apps or activities you'd like to explore?

conversationStarters.title: Curiosity Mapping
conversationStarters.message: Their recent searches include: "science homework, educational videos, math tutorials" - their mind is actively exploring!
conversationStarters.actionSuggestion: Ask: 'I saw you were curious about science homework. What sparked that interest? Want to dive deeper together?'
deeperQuestions: What questions are you trying to answer?
Have you found anything surprising or confusing?
Would you like help finding more resources about this?
enrichmentIdeas: Visit library for books on science homework
Watch documentaries together on related topics
Start a curiosity journal to track discoveries

conversationStarters.title: Finding Balance Together
conversationStarters.message: Wellness score (50.0/100) suggests room for improvement. Let's collaborate on balance.
conversationStarters.actionSuggestion: Open dialogue: 'I want to understand your relationship with screens. How do you feel after using devices?'
deeperQuestions: Do you ever feel like screen time takes away from other things you enjoy?
What would a 'balanced day' look like to you?
What boundaries might help you feel better?

conversationStarters.title: Healthy Screen Habits!
conversationStarters.message: Only 1 minutes/day - excellent balance! They're prioritizing offline life.
conversationStarters.actionSuggestion: Affirm: 'I notice you use screens mindfully and make time for other activities. What helps you maintain this balance?'
deeperQuestions: What offline activities bring you the most joy?
How do you decide what deserves your screen time?
What advice would you give other kids about screens?

syntheticReport.guidanceForParents: Your child's digital wellness score of 50.0/100 reflects moderate areas for parental guidance. Approach conversations with curiosity rather than judgment. Start by acknowledging their interests in Chrome Browser, YouTube, then collaboratively set boundaries. Create 'tech-free zones' for family connection (meals, bedtime). Use the 3 C's: Connection (understand their digital world), Collaboration (set limits together), Consistency (enforce agreed boundaries lovingly). Remember: your goal is digital wellness, not digital perfection.
